skills.tipsAndNotes:
Note: when translating from English to Swahili, numbers should be written in words. Unfortunately, most numbers past 99 are too long to fit in the hints, so those will not be included

# Numbers
1 - moja;
2 - mbili;
3 - tatu;
4 - nne;
5 - tano;
6 - sita;
7 - saba;
8 - nane;
9 - tisa;
10 -kumi;
11 - kumi na moja

20 - ishirini; 21 - ishirini na moja
30 - thelathini;
40 - arobaini;
50 - hamsini;
60 - sitini;
70 - sabini;
80 - themanini;
90 - tisini;
100 - mia moja;

1,000 -elfu moja;
10,000 - elfu kumi;
100,000 - laki moja;
1,000,000 - milioni moja;
10,000,000 - milioni kumi;
1,000,000,000 - bilioni moja;

>Note: the numbers *sita, saba, tisa* and *kumi* **never** take on noun prefixes i.e. 'Watu saba', 'Viti kumi', etc.

# Years

* 1994 - mwaka elfu moja mia tisa tisini na nne
* 1720 - mwaka elfu moja mia saba (na)* ishirini
* 2019 - mwaka elfu mbili na kumi na tisa

(na)* - not necessary

# Decimals

5.63 - tano nukta sita tatu

21.5 - ishirini na moja nukta tano
